PIDCalib
========

The scripts in this directory are for creating the PID performance histograms and the per-event PID efficiencies (weights).

To be able to run them, setup the Urania environment, clone the required repos, and build:

    $ SetupUrania v2r1 --build-env
    $ getpack PIDCalib/CalibDataScripts v4r3
    $ getpack PIDCalib/PIDPerfTools v5r4
    $ getpack PIDCalib/PIDPerfScripts v6r1
    $ cd PIDCalib/PIDPerfScripts/cmt
    $ cmt br cmt make

Finally, refresh the environment:

    $ SetupUrania v2r1

You can then symlink the files in these directory in to `$PIDPERFSCRIPTSROOT/scripts/python/MultiTrack` and run them.
